subSubSection.paragraph:
Gerrhosaurus bulsi
, sister taxon to all other taxa in the
G. nigrolineatus
complex, is well supported as a distinct lineage (
Fig. 1
), and is easily identifiable from others in the complex by its distinct, largely uniform, brown or grey dorsal colour pattern in adults (
Fig. 12
). The type locality of G. b ul s i is Dundo, north-east Angola ; the species also occurs in Zambia and the D.R.C. (Laurent 1954, 1964; Broadley 1966 ; Haagner et al. 2000 ; Broadley & Cotterill 2004 ; Adolphs 2006, 2013). Our samples were from Kalumbila Village in North West Province, Zambia ; and near Lake Carumbo, Angola , i.e. about 100 km WSW of the type locality (
Table 1
).

